                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/57.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Chihuahua</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1159fn1">Referred December 13 to the Secretaries of Labor
                        and War, and the American National Red Cross, for such action as may be
                        deemed necessary.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A considerable number of Spanish subjects will leave here tomorrow by train for
                    El Paso. I recommend that financial aid be requested <pb facs="1007" n="903"
                        xml:id="pg_903"/> from Red Cross for relief at El Paso. If possible
                    authority is requested to issue letters of identification to Spanish subjects
                    here for use at border.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
